The paper deals with the construction of spanners in Euclidean space, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of doubling metrics and the analysis of tradeoffs between parameters suggest that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). The mention of running time and optimization suggests that numerical analysis (cs.NA) may also be a relevant sub-category.
